General.Name: Netmore Group AB Series B
General.Description: Netmore Group AB (publ) operates as an internet of Things (IoT) operator. It provides Proptech and Connectivity Node, a combination of hardware and software installed in a building that offers online connectivity for systems, devices, and applications available in a building; LoRaWAN, a low power wide area networking protocol to wirelessly connect battery operated things to the internet; and LoRaWAN Portal, an easy-to-use user interface and platform to manage and control IoT devices and the network. The company also offers open access 5G networks; unified management systems to monitor and get access to all property systems, and generate reports about data usage, access, and uptime; APIs with full data access; Wi-Fi equipment for tenant, enterprise, and public; and sim cards. The company was founded in 2010 and is based in Stockm, Sweden. Netmore Group AB (publ) is a subsidiary of Buildroid Invest AB.
